 are living, and If any of\nthem are dead, their unknown\nheirs, devisees, legatees, or\ngrantees, FLORIDA REALTY\nSERVICE CORPORATION, a\ndissolved Florida corporation,\nWALTER HOFF SEELY.\nBLANCHE S. SEELY and\nNANCY S. SEELY, as the sur\nviving directors and trustees\nof FLORIDA REALTY SERV\nICE CORPORATION, a dis\nsolved Florida corporation, all\nother unknown persons or\ncorporations claiming under\nsaid defendants, or any of\nthem, either as heirs, devisees,\nlegatees, grantees, or other\nwise, and all other unknown\npersons or corporations hav\ning or claiming some estate,\nright, title or interest in the\nfollowing described property\nor any part thereof, to-w!t:\nLot 3, Section 33, Township\n66 South, Range 29 East, lo\ncated on LITTLE TORCH\nKEY, less that part of said\nLot 3 commencing at the\nnortheast corner of said Lot 3\nand running south along the\neast boundary thereof 7%\nchains, thence west, at right\nangles, to a point on the high\nwater line on the western\nshore of LITTLE TORCH\nKEY. thence meandering In A\nnortherly direction along said\nhigh water Une to a point\non the northern boundary of\nsaid Lot 3, thence east along\nthe northern boundary of Lot\n3 for a distance of 20 chains,\nmore or less, to the point of\nbeginning, said excepted por\ntion of said Lot 3 containing\nla. a\nGREETINGS:\nYOU ARE HEREBY NOTIFIED\nthat suit to quiet title has been\nbrought In the Circuit Court of\nthe Sixteenth Judicial Circuit In\nand for Monroe County. Florida, in\nChancery, against Carolyn F.\nSnyder and, if married,\nSnyder, her husband, R. W, Wat\nson and, If married. Mrs. R. W.\nWatson, his wife, John J. Darter\nand. if married, Mrs. John J.\nDarter, his wife, H. J. Scheifle\nand, if married, Mrs. H. J.\nScheifle, his wife, Clementine Por\nter and, If married, Por-\nter, her husband, Nellie Reynolds\nand, if married. Reynolds,\nher husband. Dr. E. H. Carpenter\nand. If married, Mrs. E. H. Car\npenter, his wife, I. N. Lykins and,\nif married, Mrs. L. N